BungieNet.Engine.Contract.Destiny.World..subtitle: Event Vendor
BungieNet.Engine.Contract.Destiny.World..name: Eva Levante
BungieNet.Engine.Contract.Destiny.World..description: No longer an outfitter for heroes of the Tower, Eva now devotes her time to making sure Guardians enjoy seasonal events.

interactions.flavorLineOne: You tell Eva about your meditation. She nods. "The greatest thing we can do to honor those we've lost is to live well and be our best selves. Take that armor. Go out into the world. Reforge it. Make it into a symbol of something strong and proud and beautiful."

headerDisplayProperties.description: Speak to Eva Levante in the Tower.
headerDisplayProperties.name: The End Is Nigh

interactions.flavorLineOne:
The Festival of the Lost is nearing its end. Be sure to collect any remaining masks and participate in all associated activities this week!

Happy Festival of the Lost!
"A gift need not be material. Sometimes your presence, a little favor, or some advice is just as welcome. The Dawning is a time to care for one another." —Eva Levante

Eva is delighted to see the completed blueprint. She thanks you for your hard work and rewards you with a festive sparrow.

"I'm sure this will help you show off your Dawning spirit," she says warmly.
"Exchanging presents is time-honored Festival of the Lost tradition. Bring your extra sweets to me and trade them for a gift." —Eva Levante
"The Revelry honors you and everything you do, Guardian. Celebrate it however you want. The Vanguard has helped me put together a festival across the solar system." —Eva Levante

Eva is glad to see you. She congratulates your contributions to the defense of the City, then tells you that this year's Solstice is special—Ikora, along with a small group of Warlocks, have come up with an unusual surprise… but she's not spilling the secret. You'll have to go see for yourself.

"Did Zavala like his gift?" Eva asks, and then laughs. "Whether he said so or not, I assure you he did."

She smiles. "Go on, then. Spread some cheer. You'll discover even more ingredients and recipes on your travels. I'm sure you'll find what you need to make gifts for everyone on your list."

"Isn't it a marvelous idea!" Eva exclaims as you approach. "An island in the sky. My goodness. When I was a little girl, I read stories about such things, but you Guardians can actually make them real."

She sighs, sobering as she offers you a gift: a set of ruined armor from the Red War. "But of course, the Solstice is more than just floating islands. Take this armor to the Statue of Heroes, dear. Try to think about everyone who came before you, everyone who made it possible to stand here in this Tower today…"
"Make your way to the Verdant Forest! The Vanguard and Osiris have prepared a celebration just for you." —Eva Levante

"Welcome to the Dawning, Guardian," Eva says. "At this time of year, the City joins together to celebrate and give thanks for all we have."

She smiles. "Last year, I asked Guardians to bake gifts for their friends using my Holiday Oven. I've improved the oven since then, and I would love to lend it to you again. I think you should begin by baking a gift for our dear Commander Zavala."
Welcome to the Revelry, Guardian. Here's a little pick-me-up to help your celebration along.

Eva smiles when you walk up. "Welcome," she says, and then gestures to the decorations adorning the Tower. "A beautiful transformation, isn't it? These decorations honor a yearly tradition here in the City. I am so pleased to invite you to be part of it."

"Welcome to the Festival of the Lost, Guardian," Eva says. "The people of the City use this time to celebrate life and remember the lost. We eat sweets, light candles, and wear masks to scare away our own fears."

She smiles. "The other vendors in the Tower may have some gifts for you. Go and wish each of them good tidings this holiday."
A gift from Eva celebrating the Solstice of Heroes. Refit courtesy of Amanda Holliday.
Eva beams with pride. "Well done, my dear. That kind of work ethic will carry you through your whole life… let alone the summer! Ha!"

failureStrings: Collect Majestic Solstice armor from all classes
Requires completion of the "Party Hard" Triumph.
Only available during this year's Dawning.
